1
00:00:03,671 --> 00:00:05,606
(Minseok) ⟨I lost my Japanese parents when I was young →

2
00:00:05,673 --> 00:00:08,609
I was adopted by a Korean chaebol family→

3
00:00:08,676 --> 00:00:12,613
Just as I was about to take over as president after my father...⟩

4
00:00:12,680 --> 00:00:17,118
>> Korean

5
00:00:18,085 --> 00:00:19,520
(Kyonhwa) Get out!

6
00:00:19,587 --> 00:00:23,023
(Minseok) ⟨I was chased out of Korea after being accused of embezzlement⟩

7
00:00:23,090 --> 00:00:28,029
⟨In despair, I met Dr. Momoko, a doctor at the clinic...⟩

8
00:00:28,095 --> 00:00:30,531
(Momoko) There are words that I have always cherished.

9
00:00:30,598 --> 00:00:33,534
``There is no tree that will not fall even after being cut 10 times.''

10
00:00:33,601 --> 00:00:37,538
(Minseok) ⟨I learned that she values ​​the same words as I do⟩

11
00:00:37,605 --> 00:00:41,042
(Takuto) Momoko also lost her father in an accident.

12
00:00:41,108 --> 00:00:43,043
(Minseok) A spell to cheer you up.

13
00:00:43,110 --> 00:00:46,046
There is no tree that will not fall after being cut 10 times.

14
00:00:46,113 --> 00:00:50,551
⟨Those are the words I told her 23 years ago⟩

15
00:00:50,618 --> 00:00:52,553
⟨but…⟩

16
00:00:52,620 --> 00:00:54,555
(Momoko) Takuto taught me this.

17
00:00:54,622 --> 00:00:58,626
That's why I'm grateful to Takuto.

18
00:01:08,569 --> 00:01:11,005
(Momoko) What's wrong?

19
00:01:11,071 --> 00:01:14,575
(Minseok) Ah... Ah, no.

20
00:01:19,580 --> 00:01:22,016
(Momoko) I'm sorry I had to send it to you.

21
00:01:22,083 --> 00:01:24,018
(Minseok) No.

22
00:01:24,084 --> 00:01:27,521
(Momoko) Good night then.

23
00:01:27,588 --> 00:01:29,523
(Minseok) Good night.

24
00:01:29,590 --> 00:01:38,532
♪～

25
00:01:38,599 --> 00:01:40,601
(Momoko) Minseok-san.

26
00:01:45,105 --> 00:01:49,110
(Momoko) Thank you very much for today.

27
00:01:53,113 --> 00:01:55,116
(Momoko) See you at the children's cafeteria.

28
00:01:57,618 --> 00:02:00,554
(Minseok) Yes again.

29
00:02:00,621 --> 00:02:02,556
(Momoko) Be careful.

30
00:02:02,623 --> 00:02:21,008
♪～

31
00:02:21,075 --> 00:02:23,577
(Minseok) Huh…｡

32
00:02:25,079 --> 00:02:26,514
(Apricot) Peaches!

33
00:02:26,580 --> 00:02:29,016
(Momoko) \Yes! /

34
00:02:29,083 --> 00:02:31,018
Good morning sister.

35
00:02:31,085 --> 00:02:33,020
(Kyoko) It's not "good morning."

36
00:02:33,087 --> 00:02:36,023
Are you already a 5 year old?

37
00:02:36,090 --> 00:02:37,525
(Momoko) Huh?

38
00:02:37,591 --> 00:02:40,027
>> Make it so muddy!

39
00:02:40,094 --> 00:02:42,530
(Momoko) I'm sorry.

40
00:02:42,596 --> 00:02:47,535
>> What on earth did you do to make it so dirty?

41
00:02:47,601 --> 00:02:49,537
Oh, I even got hurt.

42
00:02:49,603 --> 00:02:53,607
No... So what were you doing there?

43
00:02:56,610 --> 00:02:58,045
(Momoko) [Ah! ]

44
00:02:58,112 --> 00:03:00,614
(Minseok) [Are you okay? Let's go together]

45
00:03:03,551 --> 00:03:05,986
(Kyoko) Hey Momoko, are you listening?

46
00:03:06,053 --> 00:03:07,988
(Momoko) Yes, I'm listening.

47
00:03:08,055 --> 00:03:10,491
Ah, I'll take out the trash!

48
00:03:10,558 --> 00:03:12,993
>> Hey Momoko!

49
00:03:13,060 --> 00:03:23,003
♪～

50
00:03:23,070 --> 00:03:26,006
(Minseok) [“There is no tree that will not fall after being cut 10 times”]

51
00:03:26,073 --> 00:03:30,578
[I have lived my life valuing those words.]

52
00:03:32,079 --> 00:03:34,081
(Momoko) I see...

53
00:03:43,591 --> 00:03:46,527
(Momoko) [To cheer me up when I was in despair→

54
00:03:46,594 --> 00:03:49,096
Takuto told me]

55
00:03:54,602 --> 00:03:57,538
(Minseok) Take the elevator to the 3rd floor and turn right.

56
00:03:57,605 --> 00:04:01,041
(Female) Thank you. (Minseok) Please take your time.

57
00:04:01,108 --> 00:04:03,110
welcome.

58
00:04:06,547 --> 00:04:07,982
(Minseok) Takuto-san.

59
00:04:08,048 --> 00:04:11,485
(Takuto) Oh, as expected, he's so cool looking so stiff.

60
00:04:11,552 --> 00:04:13,487
(Minseok) Ah, no...｡

61
00:04:13,554 --> 00:04:15,489
Why are you here?

62
00:04:15,556 --> 00:04:17,992
(Takuto) Minchok!

63
00:04:18,058 --> 00:04:19,994
What time do you work today?

64
00:04:20,060 --> 00:04:21,996
(Minseok) Huh?

65
00:04:22,062 --> 00:04:25,499
(Takuto) It's almost there, it's almost there, it's almost there.

66
00:04:25,566 --> 00:04:27,568
Good.

67
00:04:33,073 --> 00:04:37,011
(Takuto) Wow, look at it, Minchok.

68
00:04:37,077 --> 00:04:39,513
That's amazing.

69
00:04:39,580 --> 00:04:43,017
The sunset you can see from here is the best.

70
00:04:43,083 --> 00:04:45,019
copper? Did you like it?

71
00:04:45,085 --> 00:04:46,520
(Minseok) Yes.

72
00:04:46,587 --> 00:04:48,522
(Takuto) Doesn't it sound like you were forced to say something?

73
00:04:48,589 --> 00:04:50,024
(Minseok) No...

74
00:04:50,090 --> 00:04:54,094
(Takuto) But Momoko often gets mad at me for being too pushy.

75
00:04:56,096 --> 00:04:59,533
But it's really amazing.

76
00:04:59,600 --> 00:05:04,972
When I look at this sunset, I can't forget what happened.

77
00:05:05,039 --> 00:05:08,542
That's why I really wanted to show it to Mincheok.

78
00:05:12,046 --> 00:05:14,048
(Minseok) Takuto-san.

79
00:05:15,549 --> 00:05:18,052
Did something happen?

80
00:05:23,057 --> 00:05:25,559
(Takuto) You know...

81
00:05:28,562 --> 00:05:32,066
(Takuto) You said you lost your parents at our hospital.

82
00:05:33,567 --> 00:05:35,002
(Minseok) Yes.

83
00:05:35,069 --> 00:05:39,006
(Takuto) What are your parents' names?

84
00:05:39,073 --> 00:05:41,075
Aoki?

85
00:05:43,577 --> 00:05:46,580
(Minseok) Why did you do that?

86
00:05:48,582 --> 00:05:53,587
(Takuto) I still have my old medical records, and I noticed this when I looked at them.

87
00:05:55,089 --> 00:05:59,093
>> [Sound of keyboard hitting]

88
00:06:04,531 --> 00:06:06,033
[Mouse click sound]

89
00:06:09,036 --> 00:06:14,475
(Minseok) Originally, my name was Teru Aoki.

90
00:06:14,541 --> 00:06:17,978
My parents died →

91
00:06:18,045 --> 00:06:21,982
I was adopted by someone who was my biological father's best friend →

92
00:06:22,049 --> 00:06:24,551
I went to Korea.

93
00:06:26,053 --> 00:06:28,055
(Takuto) I see.

94
00:06:33,060 --> 00:06:35,496
(Takuto) Then that must have been Minchok.

95
00:06:35,562 --> 00:06:37,064
(Minseok) Huh?

96
00:06:42,069 --> 00:06:45,072
(Takuto) ``There is no tree that will not fall even after being cut 10 times.''

97
00:06:48,075 --> 00:06:50,511
(Takuto) 23 years ago→

98
00:06:50,577 --> 00:06:54,581
Who taught this word to Momoko?

99
00:06:57,084 --> 00:06:59,520
(Minseok) [Hey, do you know? ]

100
00:06:59,586 --> 00:07:03,023
[Character that will cheer you up]

101
00:07:03,090 --> 00:07:07,027
[There is no tree that will not fall after being cut 10 times]

102
00:07:14,034 --> 00:07:16,970
(Takuto) Actually, me too →

103
00:07:17,037 --> 00:07:19,473
I was there that day.

104
00:07:19,540 --> 00:07:21,975
(Minseok) Huh?

105
00:07:22,042 --> 00:07:25,479
(Takuto) That day I was →

106
00:07:25,546 --> 00:07:30,984
I heard that Momoko's father was taken to our hospital...

107
00:07:31,051 --> 00:07:44,498
(Momoko) [crying]

108
00:07:44,565 --> 00:07:47,501
(Takuto's voice) But...

109
00:07:47,568 --> 00:07:50,504
Look at Momoko crying →

110
00:07:50,571 --> 00:07:53,073
I just couldn't get close.

111
00:07:56,577 --> 00:07:59,580
(Takuto) Until then, I had only seen Momoko smiling.

112
00:08:03,517 --> 00:08:05,953
(Takuto's voice) While I'm doing that→

113
00:08:06,019 --> 00:08:09,957
A boy around the same age came →

114
00:08:10,023 --> 00:08:12,960
I sat next to Momoko.

115
00:08:13,026 --> 00:08:16,463
(Momoko) [crying]

116
00:08:16,530 --> 00:08:19,967
[Thank you] (Minseok) [Yeah]

117
00:08:20,033 --> 00:08:23,537
(Nurse) [Teru-kun, I'm sorry, but could you hurry up and come here please? ]

118
00:08:25,038 --> 00:08:29,543
(Takuto's voice) After a while, a nurse brought the boy away.

119
00:08:34,548 --> 00:08:36,550
(Takuto's voice) Then...

120
00:08:38,051 --> 00:08:39,553
(Momoko) [Sound of falling]

121
00:08:44,057 --> 00:08:46,994
(Takuto) [Peach! peach! 〕

122
00:08:47,060 --> 00:08:51,498
(Momoko) [Haa haa...]

123
00:08:51,565 --> 00:08:54,568
(Takuto's voice) Momoko developed a fever and collapsed.

124
00:08:58,071 --> 00:09:02,509
(Takuto's voice) He continued to sleep like that for a long time.

125
00:09:02,576 --> 00:09:06,513
(Momoko) [Haa haa...]

126
00:09:10,517 --> 00:09:12,452
>> [Sound of door opening]

127
00:09:12,519 --> 00:09:15,455
(Female) [Kyoko-chan, are you okay? ]

128
00:09:15,522 --> 00:09:17,524
(Kyoko) [Yes]

129
00:09:22,029 --> 00:09:25,532
[Sound of door closing]

130
00:09:28,535 --> 00:09:30,537
(Takuto) [Peach? 〕

131
00:09:33,540 --> 00:09:35,475
(Peach) [Takuto...]

132
00:09:35,542 --> 00:09:38,979
[Did you stay for a long time? ]

133
00:09:39,046 --> 00:09:41,048
(Takuto) [Yeah]

134
00:09:42,549 --> 00:09:44,551
(Momoko) [Thank you]

135
00:09:47,054 --> 00:09:49,489
[Hey Takuto]

136
00:09:49,556 --> 00:09:51,491
(Takuto) [Hmm? ]

137
00:09:51,558 --> 00:09:56,997
(Momoko) [“There is no tree that will not fall even after being cut 10 times”]

138
00:09:57,064 --> 00:10:02,069
[I'll always remember these words]

139
00:10:08,075 --> 00:10:10,077
(Takuto) [Yeah]

140
00:10:18,085 --> 00:10:21,021
(Takuto) The shock of losing my father →

141
00:10:21,088 --> 00:10:24,024
Because I had a fever and was in bed →

142
00:10:24,091 --> 00:10:28,028
Momoko's memory was confused.

143
00:10:28,095 --> 00:10:32,532
but….

144
00:10:32,599 --> 00:10:36,536
I thought I would remember it someday.

145
00:10:36,603 --> 00:10:39,606
I wasn't the one who taught you those words.

146
00:10:41,608 --> 00:10:47,047
But it remained the same even when I became an adult.

147
00:10:47,114 --> 00:10:50,050
[Kampai! ] (Momoko) [Kampai! ]

148
00:10:50,117 --> 00:10:53,053
[Mmmm, delicious]

149
00:10:53,120 --> 00:10:56,056
(Takuto) [Wow, the training was tough]

150
00:10:56,123 --> 00:10:58,558
(Momoko) [Yes, but finally →

151
00:10:58,625 --> 00:11:01,061
It felt like I was standing at the starting line to become a doctor.]

152
00:11:01,128 --> 00:11:03,130
(Takuto) [Of course] (Momoko) [Yeah]

153
00:11:07,567 --> 00:11:10,003
(Takuto) [Hey...] (Momoko) [Takuto: Do ​​you remember? ]

154
00:11:10,070 --> 00:11:12,506
(Takuto) [Hmm? ]

155
00:11:12,572 --> 00:11:17,077
(Momoko) [Words that my father said to me when he was in an accident]

156
00:11:19,079 --> 00:11:24,017
[“There is no tree that will not fall after being cut 10 times”]

157
00:11:24,084 --> 00:11:30,524
[Because of these words, I did my best without giving up.]

158
00:11:30,590 --> 00:11:36,029
[I'm embarrassed to say something again, but→

159
00:11:36,096 --> 00:11:38,598
Thank you, Takuto]

160
00:11:40,600 --> 00:11:44,037
〔what? what up? ]

161
00:11:44,104 --> 00:11:45,605
(Takuto) [No]

162
00:11:47,607 --> 00:11:53,113
(Takuto's voice) Momoko always thought those were my words.

163
00:12:01,621 --> 00:12:03,557
(Takuto) You know...

164
00:12:08,562 --> 00:12:10,564
(Takuto) Could you please shut up?

165
00:12:17,571 --> 00:12:22,075
(Takuto) I don't want Momoko to go through the trouble of reminding me.

166
00:12:24,077 --> 00:12:29,082
The sadness of losing my father that day.

167
00:12:32,586 --> 00:12:38,091
(Takuto) I want Momoko to keep smiling.

168
00:12:59,613 --> 00:13:01,615
(Minseok) I understand.

169
00:13:06,052 --> 00:13:10,490
(Minseok) Me too, Momoko-sensei→

170
00:13:10,557 --> 00:13:13,560
I want you to smile all the time.

171
00:13:18,565 --> 00:13:21,067
(Takuto) Thank you, Minchok.

172
00:13:24,571 --> 00:13:29,509
(Takuto) And what if it turns out that it's actually Minchok?→

173
00:13:29,576 --> 00:13:32,512
I'm sure Momoko will blame him.

174
00:13:32,579 --> 00:13:36,016
Have you been deceiving me all this time? That's it.

175
00:13:36,082 --> 00:13:39,586
So please, Mincheok.

176
00:13:42,589 --> 00:13:45,091
(Minseok) Yes. (Takuto) Hehe.

177
00:13:53,099 --> 00:13:55,035
(Mio) Momo-chan sensei!

178
00:13:55,101 --> 00:13:57,037
(Momoko) Hello! (Mio) Hello!

179
00:13:57,103 --> 00:13:59,039
(Momoko) Are you home? Now. (Mother) That's right.

180
00:13:59,105 --> 00:14:02,042
(Momoko) See you again, Mio-chan. (Mio) Yeah, goodbye!

181
00:14:02,108 --> 00:14:04,044
(Momoko) Be careful.

182
00:14:12,552 --> 00:14:17,490
(Minseok) 《Just seeing you again is like a miracle》

183
00:14:17,557 --> 00:14:33,573
♪～

184
00:14:42,983 --> 00:14:44,417
(Minseok) Huh? 📱(vibration sound)

185
00:14:44,484 --> 00:14:48,421
📱(vibration sound)

186
00:14:48,488 --> 00:14:49,923
(Minseok) Yes.

187
00:14:49,990 --> 00:14:52,425
📱 Are you Kim Min-seok? (Minseok) Yes.

188
00:14:52,492 --> 00:14:55,428
📱 This is Tomoyama Real Estate. (Minseok) Ah.

189
00:14:55,495 --> 00:14:58,431
📱 Regarding the rental apartment you inquired about, →

190
00:14:58,498 --> 00:15:00,433
very sorry.

191
00:15:00,500 --> 00:15:03,370
📱 We already have a contract with another customer.

192
00:15:03,436 --> 00:15:05,372
(Minseok) Ah, is that so?

193
00:15:05,438 --> 00:15:07,374
📱 If I have another chance.

194
00:15:07,440 --> 00:15:08,942
📱(Sound of call being disconnected)

195
00:15:11,711 --> 00:15:13,647
📱(Real estate agent) Kim Min-seok. (Min-seok) Yes.

196
00:15:13,713 --> 00:15:16,650
📱 Sorry, the property you asked about →

197
00:15:16,716 --> 00:15:19,152
It's already decided.

198
00:15:19,219 --> 00:15:21,154
(Minseok) Is that so?

199
00:15:21,221 --> 00:15:23,156
📱 I'm sorry.

200
00:15:23,223 --> 00:15:24,724
📱(Sound of call being disconnected)

201
00:15:28,228 --> 00:15:29,729
Korean

202
00:15:31,731 --> 00:15:34,234
Korean

203
00:15:40,240 --> 00:15:41,675
📱(notification sound)

204
00:15:41,741 --> 00:15:58,191
♪～

205
00:15:58,258 --> 00:16:00,193
(Minseok) Huh…｡

206
00:16:00,260 --> 00:16:01,761
📱(notification sound)

207
00:16:10,203 --> 00:16:14,140
(Kazami's voice) ``Tomorrow is Children's Cafeteria Day.''

208
00:16:14,207 --> 00:16:28,154
♪～

209
00:16:28,221 --> 00:16:30,657
(Momoko) Good evening.

210
00:16:30,724 --> 00:16:33,159
(Minseok) Ah, good evening. (Momoko) Good evening.

211
00:16:33,226 --> 00:16:35,161
Please come up.

212
00:16:35,228 --> 00:16:36,730
(Minseok) Ah.

213
00:16:40,033 --> 00:16:43,470
(Mika) Minseok-san, thank you for coming early.

214
00:16:43,536 --> 00:16:45,472
(Momoko) That's right.

215
00:16:45,538 --> 00:16:46,973
Ah. (Minseok) Huh?

216
00:16:47,040 --> 00:16:49,476
(Momoko) The string. (Minseok) Ah.

217
00:16:49,542 --> 00:16:51,478
(Momoko) Please stay still.

218
00:16:51,544 --> 00:16:53,046
(Minseok) Yes.

219
00:16:56,549 --> 00:16:57,984
(Momoko) Yes, this is fine.

220
00:16:58,051 --> 00:17:00,987
(Minseok) Ah. (Momoko) Huh? Did it hurt?

221
00:17:01,054 --> 00:17:02,989
(Minseok) Ah, no...｡

222
00:17:03,056 --> 00:17:05,492
My back has been feeling a little tense lately.

223
00:17:05,558 --> 00:17:07,494
(Momoko) What happened?

224
00:17:07,560 --> 00:17:09,996
(Minseok) Ah, that...

225
00:17:10,063 --> 00:17:12,999
I'm currently sleeping in the break room at work.

226
00:17:13,066 --> 00:17:16,503
(Momoko) At work? You won't be able to rest at all if that's the case.

227
00:17:16,569 --> 00:17:18,004
(Minseok) Ah...｡

228
00:17:18,071 --> 00:17:20,073
(Momoko) But why?

229
00:17:23,576 --> 00:17:26,513
(Minseok) It's hard to find a house.

230
00:17:26,579 --> 00:17:28,515
(Momoko) Home? it is….

231
00:17:28,581 --> 00:17:32,018
(Mika) Yes, Momo-chan, please help me here.

232
00:17:32,085 --> 00:17:34,454
This way, this way... (Momoko) Huh?

233
00:17:34,521 --> 00:17:36,456
>> No, don't ask me any more.

234
00:17:36,523 --> 00:17:38,458
It might be about money.

235
00:17:38,525 --> 00:17:39,959
(Momoko) Ah.

236
00:17:40,026 --> 00:17:41,961
>> Prices are really high right now →

237
00:17:42,028 --> 00:17:43,963
It may be very difficult.

238
00:17:44,030 --> 00:17:45,965
(Momoko) That's right.

239
00:17:46,032 --> 00:17:47,967
Ah! >> Huh?

240
00:17:48,034 --> 00:17:51,971
(Momoko) Mr. Minseok, would you like to move here?

241
00:17:52,038 --> 00:17:53,473
(Minseok) Huh?

242
00:17:53,540 --> 00:17:55,975
(Momoko) There's a room on the second floor that I don't use and a bed.

243
00:17:56,042 --> 00:17:58,478
(Minseok) Ah, no, I think you can find it if you keep looking.

244
00:17:58,545 --> 00:18:00,480
(Momoko) Do you not like it?

245
00:18:00,547 --> 00:18:02,482
(Minseok) I don't dislike it, but...

246
00:18:02,549 --> 00:18:04,484
(Momoko) You don't have to worry about the rent.

247
00:18:04,551 --> 00:18:06,986
I wish I could help out at the children's cafeteria instead.

248
00:18:07,053 --> 00:18:09,489
(Minseok) Ah, but... (Kazami) I'm home!

249
00:18:09,556 --> 00:18:11,491
(Momoko) Ah, welcome back. (Mika) Welcome back.

250
00:18:11,558 --> 00:18:14,494
