00:36:22,281 --> 00:36:24,216
(Minseok) Manager.

504
00:36:24,283 --> 00:36:27,719
(Mizushima) Is it here? This is my new home.

505
00:36:27,786 --> 00:36:31,223
Manager: Sorry, I had some alcohol.

506
00:36:31,290 --> 00:36:33,225
I was surprised.

507
00:36:33,292 --> 00:36:37,663
Even if the heir of a wealthy family lived in a place like this.

508
00:36:37,729 --> 00:36:39,665
(Tao Zi) Yu Caoji?

509
00:36:39,731 --> 00:36:42,167
>> Heir On...

510
00:36:42,234 --> 00:36:46,171
Huh? Didn't you know?

511
00:36:46,238 --> 00:36:49,174
Yes, this person is→

512
00:36:49,241 --> 00:36:53,679
Korean conglomerate Hwangeum Hotel Group →

513
00:36:53,745 --> 00:36:59,184
He’s the heir of the family. Hahahaha…｡

514
00:36:59,251 --> 00:37:02,688
Wear it under an umbrella→

515
00:37:02,754 --> 00:37:07,192
I quickly became the deputy manager of my hotel.

516
00:37:07,259 --> 00:37:12,197
Well, I guess it's because of that margin.

517
00:37:12,264 --> 00:37:15,200
I want to start from scratch as a bellman →

518
00:37:15,267 --> 00:37:19,204
You started saying something special, haha.

519
00:37:19,271 --> 00:37:24,209
Well, I guess the same goes for living here.

520
00:37:24,276 --> 00:37:27,713
Because he is the heir of a conglomerate →

521
00:37:27,779 --> 00:37:32,718
Do you want to experience the life of common people?

522
00:37:32,784 --> 00:37:34,286
Haha.

523
00:37:35,787 --> 00:37:37,656
I'll bother you for a moment.

524
00:37:37,723 --> 00:37:39,725
(Natsume) Manager! (Minseok) Manager.

525
00:37:43,128 --> 00:37:47,065
>> Ah, sorry.

526
00:37:47,132 --> 00:37:50,569
Oh, that's cute.

527
00:37:50,636 --> 00:37:53,071
I'll bother you for a moment. (Minseok) Manager.

528
00:37:53,138 --> 00:37:55,073
(Mizushima) It's okay, it's okay... (Minseok) Manager.

529
00:37:55,140 --> 00:37:57,576
(Mizushima) Just a moment... (Minseok) Please pick it up.

530
00:37:57,643 --> 00:38:00,579
(Mizushima) Eh, children's cafeteria.

531
00:38:00,646 --> 00:38:03,081
Oh, just a little bit... (Minseok) Manager.

532
00:38:03,148 --> 00:38:06,585
>> It's okay, it's okay.

533
00:38:06,652 --> 00:38:09,588
(Minseok) Manager. >> Oh no.

534
00:38:09,655 --> 00:38:13,525
Hahahaha... The children's cafeteria is disgusting.

535
00:38:13,592 --> 00:38:17,029
Ahahaha Oh my gosh.

536
00:38:17,095 --> 00:38:20,532
Is it a charity?

537
00:38:20,599 --> 00:38:24,036
Ah, that's amazing →

538
00:38:24,102 --> 00:38:27,539
It must feel good, huh?

539
00:38:27,606 --> 00:38:32,044
Live a life without any inconvenience →

540
00:38:32,110 --> 00:38:35,047
"I'm kind →

541
00:38:35,113 --> 00:38:39,551
I'm amazing.''

542
00:38:39,618 --> 00:38:43,055
It's all a rich man's debauchery.

543
00:38:43,121 --> 00:38:48,560
You look down on us normal humans.

544
00:38:48,627 --> 00:38:53,065
Stop fooling around!

545
00:38:53,131 --> 00:38:55,634
You...

546
00:38:58,136 --> 00:39:01,640
You're such a hypocrite.

547
00:39:05,444 --> 00:39:08,146
(Minseok) Manager... (Momoko) What are you talking about?

548
00:39:10,482 --> 00:39:13,919
You don't know anything about Minseok, right?

549
00:39:13,985 --> 00:39:16,421
>> You're probably the one who doesn't know.

550
00:39:16,488 --> 00:39:18,924
You probably didn't know that this person was the heir of a conglomerate.

551
00:39:18,990 --> 00:39:22,994
(Momoko) Even if I don't know that, I know about Minseok.

552
00:39:24,996 --> 00:39:26,932
Mr. Minseok →

553
00:39:26,998 --> 00:39:29,935
He is a kind person who naturally extends his helping hand to those in need.

554
00:39:30,001 --> 00:39:32,504
(Minseok) [Help this person]

555
00:39:35,006 --> 00:39:36,942
(Momoko) Even the children know this very well.

556
00:39:37,008 --> 00:39:40,445
That's why everyone loves Minseok.

557
00:39:40,512 --> 00:39:43,949
(Child) [Amazing]

558
00:39:44,015 --> 00:39:46,451
(Momoko) For us→

559
00:39:46,518 --> 00:39:49,454
Where was Minseok born and raised?

560
00:39:49,521 --> 00:39:51,523
It doesn't matter.

561
00:39:53,024 --> 00:40:03,969
♪～

562
00:40:04,035 --> 00:40:06,471
(Mizushima) At most →

563
00:40:06,538 --> 00:40:12,410
So that you won't regret meeting this person later.

564
00:40:12,477 --> 00:40:14,413
I don't know.

565
00:40:14,479 --> 00:40:17,482
Let's go, Natsume-kun. >> I'm very sorry.

566
00:40:22,487 --> 00:40:25,424
(Sound of door opening and closing)

567
00:40:25,490 --> 00:40:27,492
(Minseok) I'm sorry.

568
00:40:32,998 --> 00:40:35,934
(Minseok) I can't say it →

569
00:40:36,001 --> 00:40:38,003
sorry.

570
00:40:47,012 --> 00:40:49,014
(Momoko) Um...

571
00:40:52,017 --> 00:40:56,521
(Momoko) Maybe I just don't understand it well.

572
00:40:58,523 --> 00:41:03,462
Even if people say that Minseok is a chaebol...→

573
00:41:03,528 --> 00:41:05,530
I don't get it at all.

574
00:41:07,532 --> 00:41:11,403
Even though you say that someone lives in a different world than you do →

575
00:41:11,469 --> 00:41:14,906
I don't think so at all.

576
00:41:14,973 --> 00:41:17,409
Minseok here →

577
00:41:17,475 --> 00:41:21,480
Because Minseok is everything to me.

578
00:41:23,982 --> 00:41:25,984
(Minseok) Momoko Sensei.

579
00:41:33,491 --> 00:41:35,427
(Momoko) I didn't need this. (Minseok) No.

580
00:41:35,493 --> 00:41:37,429
(Momoko) Huh? (Minseok) I need it. (Momoko) No, I don't need it.

581
00:41:37,495 --> 00:41:39,431
(Minseok) I definitely need it. (Momoko) I definitely don't need it.

582
00:41:39,497 --> 00:41:41,433
(Minseok) I definitely need it, no, no... (Momoko) I definitely don't need it.

583
00:41:41,500 --> 00:41:43,001
Minseok, wait.

584
00:41:49,507 --> 00:41:52,010
(Takuto) [Anosa Momoko] (Momoko) [Hmm? ]

585
00:41:53,511 --> 00:41:56,448
(Takuto) [It's about Minchok]

586
00:41:56,514 --> 00:41:58,516
(Momoko) [What's wrong with Minseok? ]

587
00:42:04,022 --> 00:42:06,958
(Takuto) [Ah, no, it's nothing]

588
00:42:07,025 --> 00:42:08,960
(Momoko) [Ah, that's right, you didn't know that, Minseok-san →

589
00:42:09,027 --> 00:42:11,463
I've just moved above the clinic.]

590
00:42:11,529 --> 00:42:14,466
(Takuto) [Eh? ] (Momoko) [So, I want you to take a look.]

591
00:42:14,532 --> 00:42:16,968
[I was thinking of giving this to Minseok]

592
00:42:17,035 --> 00:42:19,471
[Look, it's pretty expensive right now.]

593
00:42:19,538 --> 00:42:23,475
[So I thought the best way to save money would be to cook for myself.]

594
00:42:23,541 --> 00:42:26,978
[You worked really hard, didn't you?]

595
00:42:27,045 --> 00:42:30,482
[My sister came up with all this recipe...]

596
00:42:30,549 --> 00:42:40,492
♪～

597
00:42:40,558 --> 00:42:43,495
(Minseok) My real parents are →

598
00:42:43,561 --> 00:42:45,997
I was running a small coffee shop.

599
00:42:46,064 --> 00:42:48,500
(Momoko) A coffee shop?

600
00:42:48,567 --> 00:42:54,005
(Minseok) It was a place for people from the neighborhood to gather and relax.

601
00:42:54,072 --> 00:42:58,576
[When I grow up, I will protect this store]

602
00:43:06,084 --> 00:43:10,455
(Minseok) But after my parents died in an accident →

603
00:43:10,522 --> 00:43:12,958
I lost my family →

604
00:43:13,024 --> 00:43:17,462
I was taken in by my father's best friend.

605
00:43:17,529 --> 00:43:22,534
That person was the president of Hwangeum Group.

606
00:43:25,036 --> 00:43:29,975
I went to Korea→

607
00:43:30,041 --> 00:43:35,046
I started living as Kim Min-seok.

608
00:43:36,548 --> 00:43:38,550
(Momoko) That's right.

609
00:43:40,552 --> 00:43:42,487
(Minseok) Yes.

610
00:43:42,554 --> 00:43:48,560
(Momoko) I also lost my parents when I was young.

611
00:43:50,061 --> 00:43:52,497
Even with new parents →

612
00:43:52,564 --> 00:43:57,002
Even if I had a life without any inconvenience→

613
00:43:57,068 --> 00:44:03,074
I think I can at least understand the loneliness that cannot be filled.

614
00:44:08,079 --> 00:44:12,450
(Momoko) You have lived a strong life.

615
00:44:12,517 --> 00:44:25,463
♪～

616
00:44:25,530 --> 00:44:28,466
(Minseok) Welcome. Would you like to check in?

617
00:44:28,533 --> 00:44:30,468
(Male) Yes. (Minseok) I'll bring your luggage.

618
00:44:30,535 --> 00:44:33,538
(Female) Thank you. (Minseok) Please come here.

619
00:44:38,043 --> 00:44:40,478
(Kazami's voice) The heir?

620
00:44:40,545 --> 00:44:44,482
But Minseok is Minseok.

621
00:44:44,549 --> 00:44:46,985
I'll keep it a secret from my friends.

622
00:44:47,052 --> 00:44:49,554
I'm sure you'll be jealous.

623
00:44:51,056 --> 00:44:53,491
(sound of door opening)

624
00:44:53,558 --> 00:44:55,994
(Mika) Welcome back. (Kazami) Oh, welcome back.

625
00:44:56,061 --> 00:44:57,996
(Momoko) Welcome back.

626
00:44:58,063 --> 00:44:59,998
(Minseok) I'm home.

627
00:45:00,065 --> 00:45:02,000
Looks delicious.

628
00:45:02,067 --> 00:45:04,502
(Kazami) Do you want to eat? (Minseok) Ah, I'll have it then.

629
00:45:04,569 --> 00:45:06,571
I'll wash my hands before that.

630
00:45:08,573 --> 00:45:12,944
>> Ah, Minseok may have said "I'm home" for the first time.

631
00:45:13,011 --> 00:45:16,948
(Momoko) Ah. (Kazami) Ah, that's certainly true.

632
00:45:17,015 --> 00:45:20,452
Hahahaha…｡

633
00:45:20,518 --> 00:45:22,454
(sound of door opening)

634
00:45:22,520 --> 00:45:24,456
\Excuse me/ (Momoko) Hmm.

635
00:45:24,522 --> 00:45:27,459
(Mika) Sorry, it's over for today.

636
00:45:27,525 --> 00:45:30,528
(Momoko) It's okay. What happened today?

637
00:45:33,031 --> 00:45:35,033
(Eri) I'm not a patient.

638
00:45:39,037 --> 00:45:42,474
I →

639
00:45:42,540 --> 00:45:46,478
Kim Min Seok →

640
00:45:46,544 --> 00:45:48,480
I'm my fiancé.

641
00:45:48,546 --> 00:46:00,558
♪～
